            .</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17850511-39-person464">
                  SAMUEL
                   GREENHILL
               <interp inst="t17850511-39-person464" type="surname" value="GREENHILL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17850511-39-person464" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17850511-39-person464" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I lost the fowls from my hen-house, mine is a close yard, the entrance to it is through a five bar-gate, on the Tuesday morning following, I went there, but I cannot swear positively to the time.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17850511-39-person465">
                  GEORGE
                   CLERK
               <interp inst="t17850511-39-person465" type="surname" value="CLERK"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17850511-39-person465" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17850511-39-person465" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I know I marked two of these-hens, which were stolen about three weeks or a<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="178505110060"></xptr> month before they were stolen that they might be known again, they were game hens, I marked two sister hens, on the left eye, over the left nostril, and on the left foot. I cut a piece out 
the same time; I cut the comb and the gills of the cock.</p>


               <p>Where were these fowls found? - In Edgeware road, there were three live fowls and two dead, they are the same that was found upon the prisoner, he was taken the 16th of April.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17850511-39-person466">
                  THOMAS
                   ROBERTS
               <interp inst="t17850511-39-person466" type="surname" value="ROBERTS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17850511-39-person466" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17850511-39-person466" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I was with the last witness, the prisoner said first of all, he had been to Harrow to fetch them, and set out at three o'clock, and he mentioned a name which we had never heard of, then he did not know the name, and at Litchfield-street he told the gentleman he brought them from Beacon's-field.</p>


               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>Between Harrow and London, I overtook a man with two bags upon his shoulders, he said, he was going to town, and we would walk together, he said, he had fowls in his bags, I asked him what he asked for them, and I gave him fifteen pence for them.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17850511-39-verdict223" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17850511-39-verdict223" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>To be <rs id="t17850511-39-punish224" type="punishmentDescription">
